Climate change
Done by: Wissam Asfour, John Bassil, Izyan Aman, Rayyan Aman
What is climate
change?
Climate change is the major change in the
environmental conditions of the earth. Like
when it gets warmer, colder, wetter, or drier.
What will happen if it gets worse?
In the long term, The major effects of climate change can
cause:
1. Mass species extinction
2. More severe storms
3. A more acidic ocean
4. More frequent wildfires
5. Longer periods of drought
What’s the
cause?
There are many reasons why climate change exists:
1. Industrial Processes: Some industrial activities release
greenhouse gases.
2. Deforestation: stop the trees from absorbing CO2, which warms
the planet.
3.Waste Management: releases methane which traps heat
Greenhouses
Greenhouses can be very good for helping grow
plants, But some of the gases that greenhouses
produce like methane, CO2, and nitrous
gas(laughing gas), can be harmful to the planet
since they cover up the atmosphere which in turn
traps heat.

What can we do?
•The gases produced by greenhouses can be redirected into a large
container using a venting system.
•Those gases can then be separated by a process known as fractional
distillation, The separated gases can then go into their own
containers.
•Finally, The gases can be used for something that can help humans
for example, nitrous gas can be used in hospitals, especially in
surgery and dentistry; Methane can be burned to produce electricity
or power garbage trucks.
Demonstration of fractional distillation
Trade-off
Now there is a trade-off for what we can do.
If we overuse the “idea” we will end up cooling the
planet to an unhealthy level which can also affect us
humans negatively, so it is important to note that
overusing it is not a good thing.
